---
title: Pork Teriyaki with Asparagus and Sesame
description: Here's a stir fry recipe that's a little bit different. Black garlic is traditionally used in Asian cuisine and is made by heating whole bulbs of garlic over the course of several weeks, a process that results in black cloves. The taste is sweet and syrupy with hints of balsamic vinegar or tamarind, which makes it the perfect ingredient for our sweet and sticky teriyaki sauce.
